               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18290611-357-person2488">
                  SAMUEL 
                  BURTON
               <interp inst="t18290611-357-person2488" type="surname" value="BURTON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290611-357-person2488" type="given" value="SAMUEL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290611-357-person2488" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a <rs id="t18290611-357-viclabel1872" type="occupation">stationer</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18290611-357-victim2487 t18290611-357-viclabel1872"></join>. On the 11th of June, at a quarter past seven o'clock in the evening, I was on <placeName id="t18290611-357-crimeloc1873">Ludgate-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18290611-357-crimeloc1873" type="placeName" value="Ludgate-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18290611-357-crimeloc1873" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18290611-357-off1870 t18290611-357-crimeloc1873"></join> - I did not miss my pocket handkerchief, but received information, turned and followed the prisoner - he turned into a court, went into a passage, and the handkerchief was found in that passage, but I did not see him drop it.</p>
               <p>JOSEPH BROADHURST. I saw the prosecutor on Ludgate-hill; the prisoner and another young man followed him - one of the two 
               <persName id="t18290611-357-person2489">drew</persName>
             a handkerchief from the prosecutor's pocket; I ran across the road, and informed him of it - the prisoner ran; I pursued him up Ave-Maria-lane - he went into a passage of a house; he came out- I stopped him; while I held him, a gentleman in the house brought out the handkerchief - I am sure one of them took it, but I cannot say which; they were close together, and the prisoner ran into the passage.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18290611-357-person2490">
                  JAMES 
                  WILLMOTT
               <interp inst="t18290611-357-person2490" type="surname" value="WILLMOTT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290611-357-person2490" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290611-357-person2490" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. I was coming down Paternoster-row; I saw the witness with the prisoner - I came up and took him; he said, "I did not steal the handkerchief."(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I had been to Greenwich-fair, and thought I would not go to work till the morning; several gentlemen were going down Warwick-lane - I went down a turning, and was caught hold of, but I am innocent.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18290611-357-verdict1874" type="verdictDescription">
